The youth wing of Ansar-Ud-Deen Society of Nigeria (ADS) has called for the immediate release of the convener of #RevolutionNow, Omoyele Sowore and other detainees that have been granted bail by a competent court of law. Chairman of Ansar-Ud-Deen Youth Association of Nigeria (ADYAN) Northern States Council, Professor Bashir Adeniyi Omipidan noted that it was imperative for Federal Government to obey court orders and release those granted bail. Speaking ahead of ADYAN 2019 Northern State Council Conference and Awards Ceremony billed for Funtua, Katsina State, the professor of law tasked Nigerians to support President Muhammadu Buhari administration to enable it guide Nigeria to prosperity. Islamic organisation calls for release of Sowore Ansar-ud-Deen  warns  clerics against partisan politics Non-payment of Zakkat, youth exclusion worsen poverty, insecurity â€“ Ansar-ud-Deen